In article <PVmftAVBBh107h@bronze.apana.org.au>,
Dieter Jansen <dieter@bronze.apana.org.au> wrote:

>These lists of correct ECB block operations are very useful, especially
>when one is working on tuning the code, but I've never seen any examples
>of validation results for short sequences of CBC or CFB.  I know it's
>not too hard to do this by hand, but a documented standard validation
>set would be useful.  Has anyone seen one?

The libdes package available from ftp.funet.fi, as well as many
others, has such a set of examples - at least for ECB and CBC mode. I
used it recently in a little package that I wrote.


Regards,

- Andy (asb@cs.nott.ac.uk)
